A '''star map''',<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> also called a '''star chart''',<ref name="NoP">''[[Nexus of Power]]''</ref> was a [[map]] used to show the locations of celestial objects within a [[galaxy]]. The maps could be represented in a two-dimensional form or as a three-dimensional [[Holomap|hologram]] and were used in [[astrogation]], [[Navy|naval]] operations, and governmental logistics.<ref name="Tarkin" /> The [[Jedi Order]] maintained many star-charts which showed the location of legendary [[The Force|Force]] [[vergence]]s, though by the time of the [[Galactic Empire]], many of the known vergence star-charts were clever fakes. Authentic star-charts that were recovered during the era were thousands of years old, rendering them nearly impossible to interpret.<ref name="NoP" /> [[Cartographer]]s were individuals who explored and mapped [[Realspace|space]], selling their star maps to [[Spacer|travelers]] and governments.<ref name="Wild Space">''[[Adventures in Wild Space: The Escape]]''</ref> The [[Nav Guild]] was involved in recording and releasing star maps.<ref name="Rebel Files">''[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]''</ref>

